#### ListPOs(status, date_range, page)
Parameters: `$1 = status`, `$2 = date_from`, `$3 = date_to`, `$4 = offset`, `$5 = limit`
```dhl
query ListPOs(
    status: Enum(Draft, Submitted, Accepted, Cancelled, Closed),
    date_from: Timestamp,
    date_to: Timestamp,
    offset: Int,
    limit: Int
)
    private
    dhlq
    std.commerce.order.po
    | where status == $1, created_at between ($2,$3)
    | sort -created_at
    | drop $4
    | take $5
```

#### SearchPOs(q, customer_id?, status?, delivery_date_range?, has_issues?, page)
Parameters: `$1 = q`, `$2 = customer_id`, `$3 = status`, `$4 = date_from`, `$5 = date_to`, `$6 = offset`, `$7 = limit`
```dhl
query SearchPOs(
    q: Text,
    customer_id: Ref<std.iam.Identity>,
    status: Enum(Draft, Submitted, Accepted, Cancelled, Closed),
    date_from: Timestamp,
    date_to: Timestamp,
    offset: Int,
    limit: Int
)
    private
    dhlq
    search $1 in std.commerce.order.po.human_ref,std.commerce.order.po.external_id fuzz=1
    | lj std.commerce.order.po on oid=std.commerce.order.po.oid
    | where std.commerce.order.po.customer_id == $2,
            std.commerce.order.po.status == $3,
            std.commerce.order.po.created_at between ($4,$5)
    | sort -score
    | drop $6
    | take $7
```

#### FindPOsNeedingAction(type=payment_missing|allocation_needed|invoice_due|delivery_due, date_range?, page)
Parameters: `$1 = action_type`, `$2 = date_from`, `$3 = date_to`, `$4 = offset`, `$5 = limit`  
Uses a projection table of open action queues.
```dhl
query FindPOsNeedingAction(
    action_type: Enum(PaymentMissing, AllocationNeeded, InvoiceDue, DeliveryDue),
    date_from: Timestamp,
    date_to: Timestamp,
    offset: Int,
    limit: Int
)
    private
    dhlq
    std.commerce.order.po_action_queue
    | where action_type == $1, due_at between ($2,$3)
    | sort due_at
    | drop $4
    | take $5
```

#### SalesSummary(date_from, date_to, by=day|week|channel)
Parameters: `$1 = date_from`, `$2 = date_to`
```dhl
query SalesSummary(date_from: Timestamp, date_to: Timestamp)
    private
    dhlq
    std.commerce.invoice
    | where state == 'Posted, posted_at between ($1,$2)
    | bucket posted_at 1d
    | by bucket
    | agg sum(gross_amount_minor)
```

#### POCycleTimeReport(date_from, date_to)
Parameters: `$1 = date_from`, `$2 = date_to`
```dhl
query POCycleTimeReport(date_from: Timestamp, date_to: Timestamp)
    private
    dhlq
    std.commerce.order.po
    | where created_at between ($1,$2)
    | sel subject, created_at, status
```

#### CancellationReasons(date_from, date_to)
Parameters: `$1 = date_from`, `$2 = date_to`
```dhl
query CancellationReasons(date_from: Timestamp, date_to: Timestamp)
    private
    dhlq
    std.commerce.order.po
    | where status == 'Cancelled, created_at between ($1,$2)
    | agg count()
```

## Composed queries (cross-subject)

### Public composed queries
#### GetMyOrderView(po_id)
Assembled from these DHARMA‑Q queries:
```dhl
query GetMyOrderView_PO(customer_id: Ref<std.iam.Identity>, po_id: Ref<std.commerce.order.po>)
    private
    dhlq
    std.commerce.order.po
    | where subject == $2, customer_id == $1
    | take 1
```
```dhl
query GetMyOrderView_Lines(po_id: Ref<std.commerce.order.po>)
    private
    dhlq
    std.commerce.order.line
    | where po_id == $1
```
```dhl
query GetMyOrderView_Invoices(po_id: Ref<std.commerce.order.po>)
    private
    dhlq
    std.commerce.invoice
    | where po_id == $1, state == 'Posted
```

